5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE INFRASTRUCTURE LOAN PROGRAM AND
6 INFRASTRUCTURE USE FEE TAX CREDIT; REMOVING ELIGIBILITY FOR INCREASING WAGES OR
7 INCOMES OF EXISTING EMPLOYEES AND EMPLOYERS; PROHIBITING THE INFRASTRUCTURE USE
8 FEE FROM BEING CLAIMED AS A TAX CREDIT AND A DEDUCTION; AMENDING SECTIONS 17-6-309, 17-
9 6-311, AND 17-6-316, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 Section 1. Section 17-6-309, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "17-6-309. Investment preferences. (1) Subject to the provisions of subsection (2), in deciding which
15 of several investments of equal or comparable security and return are to be made when sufficient funds are not
16 available to fund all possible investments, the board shall give preference to the business investments that:
17 (a) assist employee-owned enterprises in providing new jobs or in preserving existing jobs for
18 Montana residents or in otherwise contributing to the long-term benefit of the Montana economy, including
19 raising the per capita income of Montana jobholders;
20 (b) are for locally owned enterprises that are either expanding or establishing new operations;
21 (c) provide jobs that will be substantially filled by current Montana residents as opposed to
22 providing jobs that will be filled by nonresidents coming into the state to fill the jobs;
23 (d) maintain and improve a clean and healthful environment, with emphasis on energy efficiency;
24 (e) encourage or benefit the processing, refining, marketing, and innovative use and promotion of
25 Montana's agricultural products; or
26 (f) benefit small- and medium-sized businesses as defined in rules adopted by the board.
27 (2) The board may make a loan to enhance economic development and create jobs in the basic
28 sector of the economy, as defined by the board by rule, if the loan will result in the creation of a business
