8 Section 2. Section 17-6-311, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "17-6-311. Limitation on size of investments. (1) Except as provided in subsection (2) and this
10 subsection, an investment may not be made that will result in any one business enterprise or person receiving a
11 benefit from or incurring a debt to the permanent coal tax trust fund the total current accumulated amount of
12 which exceeds 10% of the permanent coal tax trust fund. If an investment results in any one business
13 enterprise or person incurring a debt in excess of 6% of the permanent coal tax trust fund, at least 30% of the
14 debt incurred for the project or enterprise for the coal tax investment that was made to the business enterprise
15 or person must be held by a commercial lender. This subsection does not:
16 (a) apply to a loan made pursuant to 17-6-317; or
17 (b) limit the board's authority to make loans to the capital reserve account as provided in 17-6-
18 308(2).
19 (2) The total amount of loans made pursuant to 17-6-309(2) may not exceed $80 million, the total
20 amount of loans made pursuant to 17-6-317 may not exceed $70 million, and a single loan may not be less
21 than $250,000. Except for a loan made pursuant to 17-6-317, a loan may not exceed $16,666 for each job that
22 is estimated to be created. In determining the size of a loan made pursuant to 17-6-309(2), the board shall
23 consider:
24 (a) the estimated number of jobs to be created by the project within a 4-year period from the time
25 that the loan is made and the impact of the jobs on the state and the community where the project will be
26 located;
27 (b) the long-term effect of corporate and personal income taxes estimated to be paid by the
28 business and its employees;
