14 Section 3. Section 17-6-316, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "17-6-316. Economic development loan -- infrastructure tax credit. (1) A loan made pursuant to
16 17-6-309(2) must be used to build infrastructure, as provided for in authorized under 7-15-4288(4), such as
17 water systems, sewer systems, water treatment facilities, sewage treatment facilities, and roads, that allows the
18 location or creation of a business in Montana. The loan must be made to a local government or an Indian tribal
19 government that will create the necessary infrastructure. The infrastructure may serve as collateral for the loan.
20 The local government or Indian tribal government receiving the loan may charge fees to the users of the
21 infrastructure. A loan repayment agreement must provide for repayment of the loan from the entity authorized to
22 charge fees for the use of the services of the infrastructure. Loans made pursuant to 17-6-309(2) qualify for the
23 job credit interest rate reductions under 17-6-318 if the interest rate reduction passes through to the business
24 creating the jobs.
25 (2) A loan pursuant to 17-6-309(2) and this section may not be made until the board is satisfied
26 that the condition in 17-6-309(2) will be met. If the condition contained in 17-6-309(2) is not met, any credits
27 received pursuant to subsection (3) of this section must be returned to the state.
28 (3) A business that is created or expanded as the result of a loan made pursuant to 17-6-309(2)
